ground of the changing role of the Bundeswehr from 1990-2003. The book also provides unique and in-depth analysis of Germany's troubled efforts at defense sector reform in the 1990s and considers the complex politics surrounding conscription.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aNational securityzGermany. 4aInternational Relations 2019. 4aPolitical Studies 2021. 7aHISTORY / Europe / Germany.2bisacsh  a9/11.  aBosnia.  aGerman security policy.  aIraq.  aKosovo.  aWest Germany.  afirst Gulf war.  apeacekeeping missions.  astrategic culture.  awar on terrorism.1 aLonghurst, Kerry, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez978311128363040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/9781526137401zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526137401zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526137401/original  a978-3-11-128363-0 Manchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagec1986d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA